sentence: Richard Henry Dana, Jr ' s new book Two Years Before the Mast, and by Jeremiah N. Reynolds ' s account in the May 1839 issue of The Knickerbocker magazine of the hunt for a great white sperm whale named Mocha Dick, Melville and Gansevoort traveled to New Bedford, where Melville signed up for a whaling voyage aboard a new ship, the Acushnet.
